<br>
1. There are plenty of games out there on the net that allow you to do this anyway.<br>
<br>
2. I think that if this did happen Verant/sony could make the file upload easy like how are UI system works.<br>
<br>
3. There are plenty of artists who play EQ and just like with the UI skins a whole bunch of armor skins would pop up all over the net. Also UV maping is easy.<br>
<br>
4. As far as our guild we have two artists already just in our guild Syndria and myself we might have more but I am not entirley sure. If this became reality I would be happy to design armor skins for our guild on request.<br>
<br>
Incase you don't know what UV mapping is, it is a bitmap or bump map that is drawn in a certain way so that it wraps around a model. Each piece of armor is seperate in EQ ( well at least the visable piece, but thats all we are really concern with).<br>
<br>
If this becomes a reality anyone in EQ could have a more unique look and in combination with the dye system which is more of a tint system your could mess around with your look even more.<br>
<br>
What we have to do :<br>
1. The only way I am seeing this idea go from concept to reality is by having as many peeps as possible sending in this suggestion to Verant/Sony.<br>
<br>
2. To get peeps in the game to send in suggestions then we have to be active in promoting this idea to other layers in the game.<br>
<br>
3. The bestway to promote this idea is to talk to peeps online about this idea and ask them politley to send in the sugestion. Also post on the General boards for most of the servers.<br>
<br>
4. Suggestion can be submited via the feedback window in game and trhu E-mail ( which is on the EQ main site for feedback alone).<br>
<br>
We as players have a voice we enough of us voclize our want for this then Sony/Verant can hardly ignore our needs to look even more unique. Now I tip my hat off to them for adding the tint/dye system but I feel this is hardly enough. We out number them not the other way around, but we pay them to play I think it is only fair that we could at least get this to make the game more enjoyable.<br>
<br>
Please do me this favor if you like the idea. Send in E-mails and those feedbacks, talk to other players and see if they would do the same. Post on as many EQ sites as you can the more people we get on our side the better.<br>
